{"questionId":"9317","questionHtml":"<p>For this value of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;find an expression for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{f^{ - 1}}\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>f</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, stating its domain.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>Note:</strong> Interchanging <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span> can be done at any stage.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = {\\left( {{{\\text{e}}^x} - 3} \\right)^2} - 4\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msup>\n              <mrow>\n                <mtext>e</mtext>\n              </mrow>\n              <mi>x</mi>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{{\\text{e}}^x} - 3 =&nbsp; \\pm \\sqrt {y + 4} \">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>e</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>±</mo>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mi>y</mi>\n    <mo>+</mo>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>as&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x \\leqslant {\\text{ln}}\\,3\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>ln</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = {\\text{ln}}\\left( {3 - \\sqrt {y + 4} } \\right)\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>ln</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mi>y</mi>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mn>4</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>R1</em></strong></p>\n<p>so&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{f^{ - 1}}\\left( x \\right) = {\\text{ln}}\\left( {3 - \\sqrt {x + 4} } \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>f</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>ln</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mn>4</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>domain of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{f^{ - 1}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>f</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> is&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x \\in \\mathbb{R}\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" - 4 \\leqslant x < 5\">\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mn>5</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9317","referenceCode":"SPM.1.AHL.TZ0.9b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"For this value of a , find an expression for f − 1 ( x ) , stating its domain.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.14—Odd and even functions, self-inverse, inverse and domain restriction"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}